The paper deals with the problem of Reinforcement Learning (RL) using as few real-world samples as possible. This is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on navigation with a ground robot, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses Gaussian Processes (GPs) to learn the optimal policy in a real-world environment, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.NE, in that order.
